PRIVACY STATEMENT FOR THE FUSKR BROWSER EXTENSION
==================================================

1. NO TRACKING OR TELEMETRY
   Fuskr does not collect, transmit, or share any information about you or
   your use of the extension.  No analytics, crash reporters, or telemetry
   services of any kind are included.  Your browsing activity is never sent
   anywhere by this extension.

2. LOCAL STORAGE ONLY
   The extension stores your preferences (display settings, gallery history,
   and logging configuration) exclusively in your browser's local extension
   storage.  This data never leaves your device.

3. OPTIONAL DIAGNOSTIC LOGGING
   Fuskr includes an opt-in diagnostic logging feature.  It is disabled by
   default and must be explicitly enabled in the Options page.

   On Firefox 139 and later, enabling logging will display a browser-native
   consent prompt asking whether you agree to the extension collecting
   technical and interaction data.  You may grant or revoke this consent at
   any time via the "Permissions and data" tab in about:addons.

   On Chrome, the same opt-in checkbox applies; no browser-level prompt is
   shown as Chrome does not yet implement the data-collection permissions API.

   When enabled, log entries are stored locally in your browser and are never
   transmitted anywhere automatically.

4. SHARING LOGS (ENTIRELY OPTIONAL)
   If you are experiencing a problem with Fuskr and wish to help diagnose it,
   you may use the "Export Logs" button in the Options page to download a log
   file and attach it to a bug report on the Fuskr GitHub repository (bearing
   in mind that this is a PUBLIC repository).

   Before sharing any log file, please review its contents to ensure you are
   comfortable with the information it contains.  Logs may include URLs of
   images you attempted to gallery-ise and technical details about your
   browser environment.
   NEVER SHARE LOGS THAT CONTAIN INFORMATION YOU CONSIDER SENSITIVE!

   Sharing logs is entirely voluntary and is never required.

5. SUMMARY
   - No tracking.  No telemetry.  No data leaves your device automatically.
   - Logging is opt-in, local-only, and fully under your control.
   - You choose if and when to share a log file, and with whom.
